Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
delaycal_default_net_load(25.10)              delaycal_default_net_load(25.10)

Name
       delaycal_default_net_load

Syntax
        delaycal_default_net_load <load_value>

       Type: String

       Default: 0.5pF

       Sets  the  default  net  load  for  delay calculation. You can use this
       global variable to specify the default net load value that is used  for
       nets that exceed 1,000 terminals.

Example
              * The  following  global  variable sets the net load to 2 pF for
                nets that exceed 1,000 terminals:

                set delaycal_default_net_load 2pF

                The software displays the following information:

                Set Default Net Load as 2 pF.

Related Information
              * "Base Delay Analysis" chapter in the Innovus System User Guide

Related Global Variables
              * delaycal_default_net_delay

              * delaycal_input_transition_delay

              * delaycal_use_default_delay_limit

